cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new framework for training neural networks. It also involves optimization and implementation using PyTorch, which are common topics in this sub-category. The use of ODEs and adaptive time stepping suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The empirical results on CIFAR-10 indicate that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of neural networks and optimization techniques suggest that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of ODEs and optimization for a coupled system suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
